rComments: Prof. Levy knows art history really well. It's just that the 2-hour lecture cram thing up too much and there too much to learn in those hours. Prepare for continuous writing and some essays. Found it better if you study outside class to make sure you know what you wrote during the lec.

This class was the absolute worst. I understand she wants to force kids to come to her lectures, but she talks so fast and tries to cram SO many things into her two hour lectures and provide absolutely NOTHING but garbage slides as a resource. She and the TA's claim the readings are hard yet she still makes read so many a week. Literally hate her
NOTHING TO SAY

Levy is honestly extremely intelligent and you can tell she is passionate about the subject she teaches. Her lectures were great but her assignments were really complicated and had a lot of requirements. Also I felt some of the readings were too advanced for an introductory course but it was a good experience overall.

Prof. Levy is very passionate about what she teaches and does an excellent job at keeping lectures interesting Lectures were easy to follow along with her powerpoint, however, if you're not paying attention during lecture, you'll miss a lot of information as only examples and short descriptions are posted on the slides.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She was an amazing prof and very intelligible. She placed a lot of emphasis on your attendance which contributed to your overall participation mark. Both the midterm and final were open book - which was useful overall. Overall decent experience
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Can u believe a year one course got 45 on midterm and the prof did not curve up?Amazing course and the Marks was terrible on the course, if u want a great grade on your first year, dont take this stupid course with this prof. I study very hard but Levy gave me a strong hit.

Her lectures were not easy to follow since she would talk very fast and did not put much text on the power point, so if you miss what she said then you're screwed. This year was crazy, attendance was mandatory and people would still skip so she made a sign in sheet that we had to signature so she knew who came to class. I hated this class.
I'm not happy that I took this course

Intially I was hesitant to take her class but it's been my favourite and most rewarding class yet. Her lectures are easy to follow along and engaging, and unlike many other courses what I've learned in class has actually stuck with me. She's an amazing professor and if you're truly interested in learning she'll  make your time worth while.

Professor Levy is an amazing prof. She is tough and will push you to do your absolute best. GO TO OFFICE HOURS! She is incredibly helpful and will not only answer all of your questions, but she will also point you in the right direction and make suggestions to improve your ideas! You will be a better student after taking any of her courses.

Professor Levy is a very engaging lecturer. She makes the most important info clear by repeating it and relating it to themes. She was very clear about the format of the exams, and even told us the specific readings to focus on. The assignments were tough, but fun and rewarding! I learned research skills that have benefitted me to this day.
Even though the material in this course is very interesting, her instructions were unclear.

Professor Levy is an accomplished woman who is incredibly intelligent. My class had her when she came back from her sabbatical, and to be honest most of us did not remember her. The class was interesting, but most of us felt confused. The mid-term was a mess, and she was late on giving us the outline for our first paper as she was 'busy'.
Nice course and she's very passionate about the subject but very rude when you try to get help or go to her office hours

I have taken many classes with Prof. Levy. She was hard, but she is a genius and can be a great prof, if you are smart enough to follow her thought process. Numerous times she worked with me to get to a place I would have never gone alone. If you want to be challenged take her class, if you just want a bird course, take something else.

Levy is the worst Prof i have ever had. She gets extreme satisfaction making her students feel stupid. Her midterms are un fair! She is not clear in her lectures. she gave us an assignment, that she didn't lecture on. Then the day it was due, she did a lecture on it. when the info was no longer useful! She only did it to make her self look good!

I love Prof Levy.  She has incredibly high expectations of her students but makes the course requirements clear from the get go.  As for helpfulness, one needs only ask.  If you love art history, want to be challenged and are willing to work hard, you will find her classes incredibly rewarding.
Worst professor I have ever had.
Baroque is her specialty so it was a treat to have that class with her! She was clear about what to look for and there's tons to remember as with any AH course. Read the textbook, god.

shes intimidating although she is very helpful and does actually care about what students have to say. she does have a confidence about her which can be mistaken for 'snobbery'... she's passionate about her work and does look out for students. material is difficult but i've had worse.
a very boring lecturer, and is hard to listen to her voice.I thought her midterm was unfair, and made me lose interest in the course.

She gives off an air of snobbery, she epitomizes what every student in art dies not want to become, a huge snob.  As said before, she makes her students feel stupid and is not very nice when met with one on one.
